column2: Q: The scene shows two balls labeled “A”, and “B”. On the left side there is a pink gate. The solid arrows show the trajectories of the balls. Indicate your agreement with the assessment that ball “B” would have gone through the gate if ball “A” had not been present in the scene on a scale from 0 (not at all) to 100 (very much). You are only allowed to answer with a single number.
